66
00:08:34,675 --> 00:08:35,662
In brief:.

67
00:08:35,662 --> 00:08:50,950
Mistral: Europe's leading AI startup plans a €3B round at a €20B valuation – nearly doubling from the last Series C; sovereign wealth funds and global VC syndicates as investors (Bloomberg-confirmed) .

68
00:08:50,950 --> 00:09:06,237
Meta/Manus: Meta is unwinding its $2B deal with Chinese AI agent startup Manus after Beijing imposed conditions Meta found unacceptable – a textbook case of geopolitical risks in US-China AI investments .

69
00:09:07,162 --> 00:09:25,250
AI Music Flood: 44% of all songs uploaded daily to Deezer are AI-generated – around 75,000 tracks per day, of which approximately 85% of streams are classified as fraudulent (fake artists, royalty manipulation) and demonetized according to Deezer .

70
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:26,375
Tool of the Week.

71
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:33,250
Deezer AI Music Detector – Automatically identifies AI-generated songs in your streaming playlists.

72
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:44,550
Deezer has launched a free online tool that detects AI-generated music across platforms in playlists – compatible with Spotify, Apple Music, SoundCloud, and YouTube Music .

73
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:53,737
The tool supports 27 languages and is designed to simplify licensing and labeling processes for labels, platforms, and rights holders.

74
00:09:53,737 --> 00:10:01,950
Deezer itself already removes AI tracks from recommendations and editorial playlists and demonetizes fraudulent streams .

75
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:10,675
Particularly useful for music producers, playlist curators, and anyone who wants to know how much of their favorite playlist still comes from human hands.

76
00:10:10,675 --> 00:10:17,387
What sets Deezer apart from alternatives: it's the only publicly available, cross-platform tool of its kind.

77
00:10:17,387 --> 00:10:25,712
CEO Alexis Lanternier: "No other company has followed our lead yet, so we decided to give everyone control over their playlists." .

78
00:10:25,712 --> 00:10:28,537
Deezer AI Detector – TechCrunch Article

79
00:10:28,537 --> 00:10:29,687
Fail of the Week.

80
00:10:29,687 --> 00:10:34,850
"We expect our employees to use AI responsibly – including human review."

81
00:10:34,850 --> 00:10:45,562
KPMG had to withdraw its report "Redefining excellence in the age of agentic AI" this week after AI detection tool GPTZero identified inaccuracies .

82
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:58,125
Several organizations named in the report – UBS, NHS (UK), Swiss Federal Railways, and Transport for London – confirmed in writing that statements attributed to them were false or misleading .

83
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:05,275
The report apparently contained AI-generated statistics and citations that were adopted without human verification.

84
00:11:05,275 --> 00:11:12,887
Not an isolated incident: EY also withdrew a report in May 2026 due to AI-hallucinated footnotes .

85
00:11:12,887 --> 00:11:21,537
What makes this fail particularly notable: KPMG sells AI governance consulting to its clients – and failed to follow its own guidelines.

86
00:11:21,537 --> 00:11:34,750
Root Cause: LLM output was directly incorporated into the final report as research findings, without anyone contacting the cited organizations or verifying the stated figures against primary sources.

87
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:39,000
Classic copy-paste from model output without factual verification.

88
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:52,475
What We Learn: Every figure, every quote, every company name in an AI-generated document requires manual verification against primary sources – especially when the document bears the name of a Big Four firm.

89
00:11:52,475 --> 00:11:53,612
Number of the Week.

90
00:11:53,612 --> 00:11:55,550
$85,000,000,000

91
00:11:55,550 --> 00:12:06,262
OpenAI's projected annual loss for 2028 – despite approximately 900 million weekly users and a valuation of $852B .

92
00:12:06,262 --> 00:12:14,037
In the same year, the company plans to spend ~$122B on compute alone – more than the GDP of Slovakia .

93
00:12:14,037 --> 00:12:22,112
These figures are contained in the confidentially filed S-1 prospectus for the planned IPO in September 2026.

94
00:12:22,112 --> 00:12:27,100
For comparison: Amazon needed nine years to reach its first profitability.

95
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:40,075
For OpenAI, the critical question hinges on whether compute costs fall faster than user growth drives losses – and whether investors are willing to accept that for a $852B valuation.

